<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-04-27T10:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-04-27T10:45:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/4729: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-27T10:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">April 27,
                                        1927—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:30
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>112. Espinosa, Argüello, and Cordero Reyes<note n="53" xml:id="d306fn53">Dr. Leonardo Argüello, Minister of Gobernación, and Dr. Manuel
                                Cordero Reyes, private secretary to Dr. Sacasa.</note> designated by
                            Sacasa to confer with Stimson, left Puerto Cabezas this morning at 6
                            o’clock on the destroyer <hi rend="italic">Preston</hi>. They should
                            arrive at Managua, Saturday or Sunday.<note n="54" xml:id="d306fn54">i.
                                e., April 30 or May 1.</note> Stimson would be glad to be fully
                            informed as to authority discussed in his telegram 109<note n="55" xml:id="d306fn55"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_328">p. 328</ref>.</note> before their arrival.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>